nce, and the innovative style of presentation will make it vital reading for all those with an interest in the linking of culture and politics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 4aPolitics. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Archive eBook-Package Pre-2000z978311078047540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147447251740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474472517423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474472517/original  a978-3-11-078047-5  Edinburgh University Press Archive eBook-Package Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK